.SH NAME
Window.confirm \- Window: confirm() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[CR]window.confirm()\f[R] instructs the browser to display a dialog
with an optional message, and to wait until the user either confirms or
cancels the dialog.
.PP
Under some conditions \[em] for example, when the user switches tabs
\[em] the browser may not actually display a dialog, or may not wait for
the user to confirm or cancel the dialog.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
confirm(message)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]message\f[R]
A string you want to display in the confirmation dialog.
.SS Return value
A boolean indicating whether OK (\f[CR]true\f[R]) or Cancel
(\f[CR]false\f[R]) was selected.
If a browser is ignoring in\-page dialogs, then the returned value is
always \f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
if (window.confirm(\[dq]Do you really want to leave?\[dq])) {
  window.open(\[dq]exit.html\[dq], \[dq]Thanks for Visiting!\[dq]);
}
.EE
.PP
Produces:
