Firefox confirm
.SH NOTES
Dialog boxes are modal windows \[em] they prevent the user from
accessing the rest of the program\[cq]s interface until the dialog box
is closed.
For this reason, you should not overuse any function that creates a
dialog box (or modal window).
Regardless, there are good reasons to \c
.UR https://alistapart.com/article/neveruseawarning/
avoid using dialog boxes for confirmation
.UE \c
\&.
.PP
Alternatively \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] element can be used for confirmations.
